Description: Base sherd of Corinthian black-figured pottery globular aryballos; exterior: painted whirligig (counter clockwise) with dot in centre; four narrow concentric bands surrounding it; above, trace of black-figure decoration consisting of part of one human and one probably animal foot to left; base of vessel slightly flattened.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see Amyx 1988, pl. 44, nos 1a and b.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 66, no. A50)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 219, no. 25)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.130) (Phase 1)
